# Marking Engine

All student answer grading MUST use the `MarkerOrchestrator` from `@mcp-gcse/shared`. Never write raw LLM calls for marking.

## The orchestrator chain (always in this order)

```ts
import {
  DeterministicMarker,
  Grader,
  LevelOfResponseMarker,
  LlmMarker,
  MarkerOrchestrator,
  parseMarkingRulesFromPrisma,
  parseMarkPointsFromPrisma,
  type QuestionWithMarkScheme,
} from "@mcp-gcse/shared"

const orchestrator = new MarkerOrchestrator([
  new DeterministicMarker(),       // MCQ — no LLM, pure comparison
  new LevelOfResponseMarker(grader), // LoR — AQA-style level descriptors
  new LlmMarker(grader),           // written / point_based fallback
])

const grade = await orchestrator.mark(questionWithMarkScheme, studentAnswer)
```

## Building `QuestionWithMarkScheme` from Prisma

```ts
const markPoints = parseMarkPointsFromPrisma(markScheme.mark_points)
const markingRules = parseMarkingRulesFromPrisma(markScheme.marking_rules)

const q: QuestionWithMarkScheme = {
  id: question.id,
  questionType: question.question_type === "multiple_choice" ? "multiple_choice" : "written",
  questionText: question.text,
  topic: question.topic,
  rubric: markScheme.description,
  guidance: markScheme.guidance,
  totalPoints: markScheme.points_total,
  markPoints,
  markingMethod: markScheme.marking_method as "deterministic" | "point_based" | "level_of_response",
  correctOptionLabels: markScheme.correct_option_labels.length > 0
    ? markScheme.correct_option_labels : undefined,
  markingRules,
}
```

## Creating the Grader (pluggable LLM)

The backend uses `defaultChatModel()` from `packages/backend/src/lib/google-generative-ai.ts`.
The web app creates its own model via `@ai-sdk/google`:

```ts
// backend
import { defaultChatModel } from "@/lib/google-generative-ai"
const grader = new Grader(defaultChatModel(), { systemPrompt: "..." })

// web server action
import { createGoogleGenerativeAI } from "@ai-sdk/google"
const gemini = createGoogleGenerativeAI({ apiKey: Resource.GeminiApiKey.value })
const grader = new Grader(gemini("gemini-2.5-flash"), { systemPrompt: "..." })
```

## MCQ is always deterministic — no LLM

`DeterministicMarker.canMark()` returns `true` when `questionType === "multiple_choice"` and `correctOptionLabels` is non-empty. It never calls the LLM — it just compares the student's selected letter(s) against the correct option labels. The orchestrator picks it first.

## ❌ Never do this

```ts
// DO NOT write raw Gemini/OpenAI calls for marking
const result = await gemini.models.generateContent({ ... }) // ❌

// DO NOT re-implement mark point logic
if (studentAnswer.includes(markPoint.description)) { ... } // ❌
```

## Fetching from Prisma — required fields

Always select these fields when loading a mark scheme for grading:

```ts
mark_schemes: {
  select: {
    description: true,
    guidance: true,
    points_total: true,
    marking_method: true,
    mark_points: true,       // parsed by parseMarkPointsFromPrisma
    marking_rules: true,     // parsed by parseMarkingRulesFromPrisma
    correct_option_labels: true, // required for DeterministicMarker
  }
}
```
